# =============================================================
# .env.example — copy to `.env.local` (auto gitignored) and fill in.
#
# GITHUB_TOKEN is used by `scripts/fetch-github.mjs` at build time
# to read PRIVATE repositories and lift the anonymous 60/hr rate
# limit up to 5000/hr.
#
# Tokens are NEVER shipped to the browser bundle — they are only
# consumed by the Node-side build script to generate the static
# `src/data/github-repos.generated.ts`. The public output only
# contains repo metadata you have already chosen to display.
#
# HOW TO CREATE A TOKEN
#   1. https://github.com/settings/personal-access-tokens
#   2. Click "Generate new token" → "Fine-grained"
#   3. Token name:         velorah-site-build
#      Expiration:         90 days (or Custom)
#      Repository access:  "Only select repositories"
#                          → select `resumeflow` and `travel-plan`
#      Repository permissions:
#                          - Metadata: Read-only   ✓ (required)
#                          - Contents: Read-only   ✓ (lets the
#                                                    script read
#                                                    README in
#                                                    the future)
#   4. Click "Generate token" and copy the `github_pat_…` value.
#   5. Paste it below, save as `.env.local`.
#
# Classic PATs work too (`ghp_…`); scope `repo` is required.
# =============================================================

GITHUB_TOKEN=github_pat_REPLACE_ME_WITH_YOUR_TOKEN
